fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.events

Class EventSink

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.events.EventSink
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CallableEventAtomicSink

    public class EventSink
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The class EventSink implements an event sink to an importing model taking an event of the source event type and providing a corresponding event of the sink event type.

    Description

    Invariant

     invariant      importingModelURI != null
 invariant      sourceEventType != null and sinkEventType != null
 invariant      converter != null
 invariant      converter.getDomain().isAssignableFrom(sourceEventType)
 invariant      sinkEventType.isAssignableFrom(converter.getCodomain())

    Created on : 2018-05-02

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      EventSink(java.lang.String importingModelURI, java.lang.Class<? extends EventI> eventType)
      create an event sink where the type of events is the same between the source and the sink.
      EventSink(java.lang.String importingModelURI, java.lang.Class<? extends EventI> sourceEventType, java.lang.Class<? extends EventI> sinkEventType)
      create an event sink where the type of events from the source is different from the one going to the sink but where no conversion is needed.
      EventSink(java.lang.String importingModelURI, java.lang.Class<? extends EventI> sourceEventType, java.lang.Class<? extends EventI> sinkEventType, EventConverterI converter)
      create an event sink where the type of events from the source is different from the one going to the sink and require an explicit conversion.
